pipeline_summary.name: PM2.5_Risk_Alert_Pipeline
pipeline_summary.description: Sequential ETL pipeline that scrapes Mahidol University AQI data, transforms it to JSON, loads it into PostgreSQL, and sends email alerts when PM2.5 exceeds thresholds.

components.name: Extract Mahidol AQI HTML
components.description: Scrapes the Mahidol University AQI webpage and saves the raw HTML to a local file.

components.name: Transform HTML to Structured JSON
components.description: Parses the saved HTML, extracts AQI metrics, validates freshness, and writes a structured JSON file.
inputs: existing JSON file for duplicate detection

connections.purpose: read raw HTML and write JSON

components.name: Load AQI Data to PostgreSQL Warehouse
components.description: Inserts the structured AQI JSON into dimension and fact tables in PostgreSQL, handling conflicts and data cleaning.
outputs: Rows inserted into dimDateTimeTable, dimLocationTable, dimMainPollutionTable, factmahidolaqitable

connections.purpose: write to dimension and fact tables

components.name: PM2.5 Email Alert Notification
components.description: Evaluates AQI thresholds from the JSON data and sends email alerts via SMTP when levels exceed safe limits.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful load to PostgreSQL; skips if AQI is within safe range.

connections.purpose: read JSON, recipient list, and email config
send email alerts via Gmail SMTP
